## Part 6: Core Design Principles

### Mobile-First Responsive Design
```
Breakpoints (test every change at ALL sizes):
- 320px  → Mobile small (iPhone SE)
- 375px  → Mobile standard (iPhone 14)
- 768px  → Tablet
- 1024px → Desktop small
- 1440px → Desktop large
```

### Performance Standards (Non-Negotiable)
```
- LCP (Largest Contentful Paint): < 2.5s
- CLS (Cumulative Layout Shift): < 0.1
- INP (Interaction to Next Paint): < 100ms
- Lighthouse Score: ≥ 90 in all categories
```

### Accessibility Standards (WCAG 2.1 AAA)
```
- Color Contrast: 7:1 ratio minimum for text
- Touch Targets: 48×48px minimum on mobile
- Keyboard Navigation: All interactive elements accessible
- Screen Readers: Semantic HTML + ARIA labels on all media
- Focus States: Visible 2px ring (black or white depending on context)
- Reduced Motion: Respect prefers-reduced-motion
```

### Luxury Perception Architecture
```
- White Space: 40%+ negative space required
- Color Palette: 11 colors maximum (see tokens below)
- Typography: Serif headlines + sans-serif body
- Animation: Slow, intentional (200-300ms), spring-based
- CTAs: Black/white luxury palette — no garish orange/red buttons
- Imagery: High-quality WebP, editorial feel, no stock photos
- Copy: Concise, confident, no hyperbole or marketing speak
```

