## Part 14: Forbidden Patterns

### Copy/Messaging
```
❌ "Maximize", "boost", "elite", "world-class", "mastery"
❌ "Sign up now!", "Don't miss out!", "Limited time!"
❌ Fake scarcity or urgency
❌ Generic marketing speak
❌ Exclamation points in headlines
❌ "AI slop" language that sounds generated

✅ "Book a Trial", "Start Training", "Join the Community"
✅ Calm, confident, specific language
✅ Founder's authentic voice
```

### Code
```
❌ Inline event handlers (onclick="...")
❌ Removed focus outlines
❌ Images without alt text
❌ Horizontal scroll on mobile
❌ Animations without reduced-motion support
❌ Hardcoded prices outside data files
❌ Stock photos
❌ More than 11 colors
❌ Space Grotesk, Inter, Roboto, Arial, Playfair Display, Work Sans fonts
❌ Hardcoded prices outside /data/*.json files
❌ Duplicate content across pages
❌ Generic emoji icons (🎾 ⭐ etc.)
❌ Footer or dark-section text below text-white/50 (fails WCAG 7:1)
❌ Hero primary CTA with only text color on dark gradient (use solid bg)
❌ Webhook: using payload ID in URLs/bodies without validating as positive integer
❌ Webhook: comparing secret with == or === (use crypto.timingSafeEqual, same-length buffers)
```

---

## Part 15: Workflows

### Code Creation
1. **Analyze Requirements**: Understand the core problem.
2. **Verify APIs**: Check documentation or run quick tests to ensure library methods exist.
3. **Design for Uniqueness**: Avoid default layouts. Think Aman/Four Seasons.
4. **Implementation**: Write clean, modular code.
5. **Review**: Self-review against the hallucination prevention checklist.

### Code Review
When reviewing existing code:
1. Check for **SOLID** violations.
2. Identify **DRY/KISS** improvements.
3. Suggest **unique design** refinements for UI components.
4. Verify all external calls are valid.
5. Ensure single source of truth for data.

